race.comment: STAR DECORUM (12) got things back on track last time at Wentworth when missing by just a long neck over a similar trip. Kept fresh for this and gets in light at the weights. Ready to break a long run of outs. RAZELLA (5) was narrowly denied when resuming at Clare before going amiss second-up here. Worth forgiving that effort, and with Milnes booked from an inside draw she can bounce back sharply third-up. MAHENO (4) improved last time when chasing gamely into fourth here. Strips fitter again and is open to further progress. Can play a role. ELEANOR QUEEN (11) failed to fire fresh when getting too far back, but with that run under her belt and stepping out to a winning trip, she can improve sharply.
